.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B CC
Default C compiler to use if \-\-cc option is not specified
.TP
.B CFLAGS
Additional flags to pass to the C compiler
.SH BUILDING ZEN-C
.PP
To build the Zen\-C compiler itself:
.PP
.RS
.nf
# Build with GCC (default)
make

# Build with Clang
make clang

# Build with Zig
make zig

# Build with TCC
make tcc

# Run tests
make test

# Clean build artifacts
make clean
.fi
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Successful program execution
.TP
.B 1
Compilation or runtime error
.TP
.B 2
Invalid command line arguments or options
.SH DIAGNOSTICS
The compiler provides detailed error messages including:
.IP \(bu 2
Line and column numbers for syntax errors
.IP \(bu 2
Type mismatch information
.IP \(bu 2
Undefined symbol references
.IP \(bu 2
Memory management warnings
.SH COMPATIBILITY
Zen\-C generated code is compatible with:
.IP \(bu 2
GCC 4.8 and later
.IP \(bu 2
Clang 3.5 and later
.IP \(bu 2
Zig cc (latest stable)
.IP \(bu 2
TCC (Tiny C Compiler)
.IP \(bu 2
MSVC (Microsoft Visual C++)
.PP
Generated C code conforms to C99, C11, or C17 standards.
.SH NOTES
.PP
Zen\-C is designed to be a zero\-cost abstraction layer over C. The transpiler generates 
clean, readable C code that can be inspected, debugged, and optimized using standard C tools.
.PP
All libraries are allocator\-aware, allowing custom memory allocators to be specified.
.PP
The project is under active development with weekly updates planned.
